methods based on the use of histograms of wavelet coefficients allow to
avoid these scaling problems. These methods are the Wavelet Profile
Method (WPM) [3] and the Leaders Profile Method (LPM) [2]. They provide
an intuitive way to make the distinction between mono and multifractal
signals. In particular, they do not rely on the usual technique involved
in the WLM for example.   In this work, we show that this approach
applied on Mars Orbiter Laser Altimeter (MOLA) data allows to have
additional information on the topography of Mars compared to the usual
methods. \{References :\}  A. Deliege, T. Kleyntssens, and S. Nicolay,
\{\vphantom{\}}Mars Topography Investigated Through the Wavelet Leaders Method: a
Multidimensional Study of its Fractal Structure\vphantom{\{}\}, Planetary and Space
