ratio and lithospheric basal slope as a function of internal Rayleigh
number and viscosity contrast, we estimate lower bounds to these
parameters of 107and 105, respectively. Several
lines of evidence point to values near these lower limits, which puts
Venus in the sluggish-lid regime of convection. There also exist several
accumulations of crustal material, most notably Ovda Regio, where there
may be as much as 90 km of crust.},
